        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> Hey.</P><P>The scariest thing for me in this petition thread, was the suggestion that it be locked, against the posibility, that anyone would dare to disagree.  This is all the more surreal, when it was a druid that was disagreeing.  <i>(You could make a strong argument that if it were, say a necromancer, making remarks like, "I hate Druids. Over powered as it is and yet they still ask to be even more group friendly," that this was just a cross class issue.)</i></P><P>I don't play a druid and I don't group enough to go criticising which classes are, or aren't balanced, really.  <i>(I do carry the standard annoyance at trying to hunt something, only to find that a druid is hogging all the spawns, but what can ya do?  (I'm compensated for this by watching quad kiters get ripped to shreds, every so often, when they run outta mana.))</i>  And, I only tend to browse other classes forums, on occaisions such as this, where a link is posted.  However, I have noticed that almost invariably, the link is always accompanied by derision of whatever class it is who feel the need improving.  The general response here seems to be almost that druids deserve to beaten soundly with the nerf bat, rather than improved in any way.</P><P>The curiousity in this, is that I'm fairly sure that if I was to hunt around a bit, I could probably find the occaisional thread on other classes boards, that does the same thing.  <i>(Posts linking to here, so everyone can deride what the 'stupid necros' want.  Posts linking to mage boards, so people can laugh that mages think their pet is underpowered.  You know what I mean.)</i>  This can't possibly help anyone.  All that this leads to is that no-one gets anything.  <i>(Druids get nothing, 'cos we have announce they need whupping with the nerf bat.  Necros get nothing, 'cos druids announced that we need an equally sound whupping with the bat.  Mages get nothing, 'cos everyone has pet envy.  And so on.)</i></P><P>After all, this <b>is</b> how nerfs happen.  You remember Mrylokar's dagger?  It didn't get nerfed 'cos the guy who got it stanted sending tells to GMs explaining it was too powerful.  It was nerfed, because a million and one people, who saw it on sites like Allakhazam's, starting bitching about it.  <i>(I find it extremely hard to believe that Verant's QA group did this off their own back, because if that was the case, it'd have been 'fixed', before it went live!)</i></P><P>I know full well that it's not gonna happen, but I genuinely believe that we'd get a whole lot further, if everyone wasn't busy tryin' to shout everyone else down.  </P><P>I'm also inclined to believe that no druid really expects to get the whole of their list of requests.  <i>(Well, some of them no doubt do, but there's never a shortage of idiots, playing any class.)</i>  A round of balancing is coming up and it's like a kid's Christmas list.  This is the list of presents they want.  If they get a coupla things, no doubt they'll be happy.</P><P>Curiously, everyone seems to have missed the root of this petition.  At the very base of the issue, is the argument, "Norrath has gotten tougher and we haven't!"  This is the same problem necromancers are bitching about.  <i>(And, though I don't know it for sure, I'd be willing to gamble, the same problem as everyone else who currently feels underpowered.)</i></P><P><i>"Druids whining for enhancements is a frigging joke on a monumental scale."</i><BR>How many boards do you suppose I could find the same remark on, but directed at necromancers?</P><P>Anyhow.  I can't see this being a popular line of thought.  Added to which, I'm bored and the servers should be comin' up soon...</P><P>*Shrug*</P><P>AlAaraaf.</P><P><BR> </font></td>
