        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'
 nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Araxx</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> Hello.<BR>Druid here.<BR>Just a comment on the druid petition some posters here are obviously not aware of.<BR>Druids are not overpowered. We have our limitations. A lot of them. As we all know we are jack of all trades, we can do a lot (not everything mind you) and the reason for this is not so we can go out and quad, but to help fill in the gaps a group might have while hunting in a dungeon or dangerous zone, or in a big raid, although that is unlikely (yet I have seen it).<BR>To put forth an example, necros are better soloers than druids, wizards are better porters and quadders than druids, Shammans are better buffers and debuffers than druids, Clerics are better healers and HP/AC buffers than druids, and I could go on naming specifics, but that would be too tiresome.<BR>We do have some good tools at our disposal, but, at the end of the day, when that big raid is forming to kill some uber boss mob, it is very unlikely a druid will be missed, not even for porting reasons. We do not have that 'one' essential buff/role/skill necessary to make a raid complete. We can fill gaps, barely, but aren't really a needed class.<BR>That petition, if it is not clear, was thought out by some very good players, who happen to be druids, and is not a petition signed by ALL the druids of Norrath across every server. It has been apparent for some time that until someone points out there is a problem, Verant doesn't listen. So we grabbed the bull by the horns and decided to do something about it. If you feel unhappy you should do the same, not whine at someone else's initiative.<BR>And to dismiss a lot of the myths out there, here is a rundown of where you are all wrong about our skills and spells:</P><P>Heals: Druids have a 10% healing penalty. So, if a heal is supposed to heal for 800, it only does for 720.</P><P>Root: C'mon! It is widespread knowledge our root is the worse one in the game! It can be resisted and has more chances of breaking.</P><P>DoTs: Our dots are NO WAY close toa  Necro's or a Shamman's. My best dot, Winged Death, which I get at 53, does 1287 damage. A Necromancer of the same level can land 2 dots on a mob that do more than 1000 damage, and I'm not even gonna mention Splurt!</P><P>Charm: This is just laughable! Our pet charm is just ridiculous. Not even worth mentioning.</P><P>Epic: LOL! Did you guys realise it gets resisted more than anything in the game? It has a snare and a dot. if one gets resisted both do. Imagine using this on a mob immune to movement... Worthless.</P><P>And to all those losers out there that keep on repeating like a scratched record 'I hate Druids', you should really go visit the brain doctor... again, and get a life too. I was warned against druids when I began playing EQ, and I can agree there are some really lousy druids out there, just like there are Bards, Clerics, Shammans, Rogues, Rangers, Beastlords, Monks, Warriors, oh, and Necros too. Realise one thing, it is not the Druid playing the human, it is the human playing the Druid, and MANY times, a human who plays a Warrior, Cleric, etc. decides to create a druid to 'go farm stuff', THAT is the lousy player. Not the class. You may say they go hand in hand. But that is your worthless opinion. IMO a Necro is far better versed in the art of farming than a Druid is.<BR>Personally I get on great with any number of 'people' in Norrath, be they Clerics, Wizards, Necros, Warriors, etc. I don't make the distinction because of the class, I make the disticntion because of the player. Something A LOT of you could learn to do.</P><P>Ciao for now!</P><P>Araxx Darkroot - 55 Preserver<BR>Clan of the Roc<BR>Bristlebane (funnily enough I know Draknn who began this thread, and have raided with him - small world)</font></td>
