and with the mass group buff AA skill you need one(1) druid to buff the whole raid.  SoW, SoE don't work in dungeons.</P><P>2/ Lull: These spells are awesome except that 1. They don't work in dungeons. 2. There are Harmony resistant mobs in Luclin.  Other than that yes they rock but honestly the only time I use it is for General raids :/.</P><P>3/ Heals: We aren't asking to be able to heal the main tank by any means; what we need is to be able to keep up with AE and heal that cleric that gets aggro.  With some of the mobs now there is no way to do that, especially when casters are topping 3500hp+. I realize that if we get a better heal it will make clerics less desirable for exp groups, but I for one am SICK of people saying "we can't go there without a cleric".  Maybe cleric direct heal needs some work also.</P><P>4/ DD: No argument from me here because I don't have the higher level DDs.  They seem fine to me now but /shrug I haven't used so I don't know and will take the word of the higher druids.</P><P>5/ Snare: Essential when it works but there are movement resistant mobs now (even in FG for exp I have seen these).  Also, Rangers and Necros can and have snared on raids I have been on (when I was playing a needed class :p). Heck, our SK puller snares sometimes.</P><P>6/ Track: A joke ability used to track named mobs you are after; other than that it does nothing.  You can't use it to monitor for adds because it sucks. I have tried tracking group members before and gone to a loc not even close to where they were.</P><P>7/ Debuff: No argument here either except that it is only fire debuff.  We have a level 49 cold debuff but it gets resisted alot and has a short duration which makes it worthless.  Bad thing about this is you only need one druid on a raid to handle this also.</P><P><BR>8/ DoT:  No argument there either.  Personally I would love to have a better DoT (who wouldn't :p) but for the purpose of the petition I think it is just a little bonus.  Having the snare effect on our epic removed and the duration decreased would be nice.  For those that don't know our epic snare lasts 3 minutes and if the mob is immune to runspeed changes our epic will never stick, making it useless.</P><P></P><P>For some reason there is a perception that druids are highly wanted in the end game; where does this come from?  The only time I have seen a druid wanted in a group is for HS or The Hole, places that aren't very fun to get out of.  Even then, you can have a wizzie and get more damage and still have snare.  The tells I get while lfg on my druid are "since you haven't found a group yet could you port me to such and such?"  On the other hand, last week in Chardok I had just logged in my cleric and rogue (two comps).  My cleric was ressing people at IZ whos cleric had died.  While rezzing them I got a tell on my cleric "fort group could use you if you are lfg" AND 2 tells on my rogue who was lfg; 1. "Do you have your HS key?" and 2. "BK/Capt. could use you".</P><P><BR>   These are the dilemmas that druids face; I have no idea where this perceived "druids are highly desired in the high end game" comes from.  I'm not saying that necros don't have a problem, or magicians for that matter, but there is a problem with the high level game where mob damage output and hitpoints have increased at a faster rate than our spells have.</P><P><BR>Let the discussion continue :).</P><P>Niner</P><P> </font></td>
