        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'> Hello friends and enemies,</P><P>I have been forced to a horrible relization. In order to strive to keep my class of choice alive I have to break my own principles - that sort of smarts.</P><P>I can't stand censorship for reason's alluded to earlier in this post.</P><P>VI/SOE message boards are censored (moderated is just another word for censored :().</P><P>Yet the only way we have to talk to them is via their totally censored message boards. My quandry is thus - do I post there and break my own anti-censorship principle. Or do I remain silent on their boards and watch my class die out completely?</P><P>I have decided on what I think is a morally acceptable solution it is documented in this post.</P><P><a href="http://necro.eqclasses.com/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=2631" target="_blank">http://necro.eqclasses.com/topic.asp?TOPIC_ID=2631</a></P><P>To Araxx,</P><P>Though I am inclined to feel that Tan goes over the top a little I entirely understand where he/she is coming from. Forget reality for a second and think EQ. Tan is a necro - he/she like all intelligent necros sees the writing on the wall. The necro class is dieing out.</P><P>To see a petition full of what we as necros (perhaps incorrectly) see as completely over the top requests to ENHANCE an already functional class receive the attention that it has is like waving a red flag at a bull.</P><P>Necro's and Mages are about to die out completely - that is a very real fact of life in the end game. The only necros that will persist are the die hard soloers and guess what? I despise them. If I wanted to play a single player game (AKA Solo) I would not buy a subscription based MMRPG like EQ. IMHO those die hard solo necros are the kind of players that really don't want to do anything for anyone else and I just can't grasp why they play an interactive game like EQ (well I have my suspisions but I'm not going into them here..).</P><P>Druids on the other hand are in absolutely no danger of dieing out in EQ. Their numbers get larger and larger as almost every player realizes their power, solo and grouped, questing, porting etc. Druids, imho, do not **need** the things they are demanding and if they are granted them before necros and mages are fixed, which is our necromancer dread, that is horribly unjust of "the powers that be".</P><P>Tell me truly Araxx, if you were fighting for your life and saw the life blood that might sustain you (coding effort on VI's part being the blood) being funneled to a healthy, fat, overweight, middle aged recipient in no need of it other than to improve his/her self image (the druids petition) would you not fight tooth and nail for it........?</P><P>That is where Tan is coming from and I understand him/her (damnit I wish english had a gender free singular word for that :)!) completely becuase I feel the same way.....</P><P> </font></td>
      </tr>
    </table>
    </td>
  </tr>
</table>
</font>

